   1:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c **** /**
   2:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   ******************************************************************************
   3:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   * @file    system_stm32n6xx_ns.c
   4:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   * @author  GPM Application Team
   5:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   * @brief   CMSIS Cortex-M55 Device Peripheral Access Layer System Source File
   6:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *          to be used in non-secure application when the system implements
   7:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *          the TrustZone-M security.
   8:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *
   9:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *   This file provides two functions and one global variable to be called from
  10:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *   user application:
  11:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *      - SystemInit(): This function is called at non-secure startup before
  12:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *                      branch to non-secure main program.
  13:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *                      This call is made inside the "startup_stm32n6xx.s" file.
  14:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *
  15:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *      - SystemCoreClock variable: Contains the core clock (HCLK), it can be used
  16:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *                                  by the user application to setup the SysTick
  17:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *                                  timer or configure other parameters.
  18:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *
  19:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *      - SystemCoreClockUpdate(): Updates the variable SystemCoreClock and must
  20:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *                                 be called whenever the core clock is changed
  21:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *                                 during program execution.
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccbc6gyF.s 			page 2


  22:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *
  23:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *   After each device reset the HSI (64 MHz) is used as system clock source.
  24:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *   Then SystemInit() function is called, in "startup_stm32n6xx.s" file, to
  25:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *   configure the system clock before to branch to main secure program.
  26:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *   Later, when non-secure SystemInit() function is called, in "startup_stm32n6xx.s"
  27:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *   file, the system clock may have been updated from reset value by the main
  28:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *   secure program.
  29:Core/Src/system_stm32n6xx_ns.c ****   *
